### Unified AI Gateway - Phi-4 Tests
### 
### This test collection validates the Phi-4 model using Microsoft Foundry for Inference chat completions API.
### 
### Prerequisites (see ReadMe for details):
### 1. Run `azd up` to provision the infrastructure and create the VS Code settings file with all required variables
### 2. Ensure your APIM instance and phi-4 Foundry backends are successfully deployed
###
### Usage:
### - Click "Send Request" above each request in VS Code with REST Client extension
### - Expected debug headers are documented for each test to validate routing behavior
### - For tests that require JWT bearer token authentication, run Authentication Stup to generate the JWT token first
### - JWT tokens expire; if you get 401 errors, re-run request to refresh the token

# Variables from VS Code REST Client settings
@apimEndpoint = {{apim_gateway_url}}/unified-ai

# APIM subscription key from VS Code settings
@apimSubKey = {{apim_subscription_key}}

# Use dynamic token from the authentication request below:
@jwtToken = {{getJwtToken.response.body.access_token}}

###############################################################################
### Authentication Setup - JWT Bearer Token Generation
###############################################################################

### Get Bearer Token for JWT Authentication
# @name getJwtToken
# Uses actual values from VS Code settings - no manual configuration needed!
POST https://login.microsoftonline.com/{{tenant_id}}/oauth2/v2.0/token
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

grant_type=client_credentials
&client_id={{entra_app_id}}
&client_secret={{entra_app_client_secret}}
&scope={{entra_app_identifier_uri}}/.default

### The access_token is automatically assigned to @jwtToken variable above
### Make sure to run the "Get Bearer Token" request first before running JWT tests
### Note: JWT tokens expire and will need to be refreshed periodically by re-running this request

###############################################################################
### Phi-4 Inference Chat Completions API Tests
###############################################################################

### Foundry Phi-4 Chat Completion With API Key
# Estimate token usage based on your request content; compare your estimates against the X-Prompt-Tokens, X-Completion-Tokens, and X-Total-Tokens response headers.
# Expected Debug Headers:
# UAIG-Auth-Type: api-key
# UAIG-Selected-Backend: inference-backend
# UAIG-Selected-API-Version: 2024-05-01-preview
# UAIG-API-Type: inference 
# UAIG-Model-ID: phi-4
# UAIG-Forwarded-Path: /models/chat/completions
POST {{apimEndpoint}}/models/chat/completions?api-version=2024-05-01-preview
api-key: {{apimSubKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "messages": [
        {
            "role": "user",
            "content": "Explain what Microsoft Foundry is in exactly 3 sentences."
        }
    ],
    "max_tokens": 100,
    "temperature": 0.3,
    "top_p": 0.8,
    "presence_penalty": 0,
    "frequency_penalty": 0,
    "model": "phi-4"
}

###

### Foundry Phi-4 Streaming Chat Completion With API Key
# This test validates Server-Sent Events (SSE) streaming for Phi-4
#
# Expected Debug Headers:
# UAIG-Auth-Type: api-key
# UAIG-Selected-Backend: inference-backend
# UAIG-Selected-API-Version: 2024-05-01-preview
# UAIG-API-Type: inference 
# UAIG-Model-ID: phi-4
# UAIG-Is-Streaming: true
# UAIG-Request-Timeout: 360 (120 base * 3 streaming multiplier)
# UAIG-Forwarded-Path: /models/chat/completions
#
# Expected Streaming Response Validation:
# 1. Response Headers: Content-Type should be "text/event-stream" with Transfer-Encoding: chunked
# 2. Response Body: Multiple "data:" prefixed JSON chunks arriving incrementally
# 3. Each chunk contains: {"id":"...","object":"chat.completion.chunk","choices":[{"delta":{"content":"..."}}]}
# 4. Final content chunk has: "finish_reason": "stop"
# 5. Stream terminates with: data: [DONE]
#
# NOTE: The complete response is distributed across all chunks. Concatenate the "delta.content" 
# values from each chunk to reconstruct the full response text.
POST {{apimEndpoint}}/models/chat/completions?api-version=2024-05-01-preview
api-key: {{apimSubKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "messages": [
        {
            "role": "user",
            "content": "Say goodbye in 5 words."
        }
    ],
    "max_tokens": 20,
    "temperature": 0.3,
    "top_p": 0.8,
    "presence_penalty": 0,
    "frequency_penalty": 0,
    "model": "phi-4",
    "stream": true
}

###

### Foundry Phi-4 Chat Completion With JWT
# Estimate token usage based on your request content; compare your estimates against the X-Prompt-Tokens, X-Completion-Tokens, and X-Total-Tokens response headers.
# Expected Debug Headers:
# UAIG-Auth-Type: jwt
# UAIG-Selected-Backend: inference-backend
# UAIG-Selected-API-Version: 2024-05-01-preview
# UAIG-API-Type: inference 
# UAIG-Model-ID: phi-4
# UAIG-Forwarded-Path: /models/chat/completions
# NOTE: You will receive a 401 response if either you haven't obtained a token (see first request) or the token is expired
POST {{apimEndpoint}}/models/chat/completions
Authorization: Bearer {{jwtToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "messages": [
        {
            "role": "system",
            "content": "You are a helpful AI assistant. Be concise and precise."
        },
        {
            "role": "user",
            "content": "Write a simple Python function that adds two numbers."
        }
    ],
    "max_tokens": 150,
    "temperature": 0.1,
    "top_p": 0.9,
    "presence_penalty": 0.1,
    "frequency_penalty": 0.1,
    "model": "phi-4"
}

###
